# Toast usage (frontend)

This app does not yet ship `sonner` or `toast-helpers`. When you add notifications:

- Add a single module (e.g. `app/utils/toast-helpers.ts`) that wraps your toast library.
- Do **not** import `toast` from `sonner` (or equivalent) directly across components; import helpers only.

## Intended helpers (match before merge)

- `showError(message)` — failures / negative outcomes
- `showSuccess(message)` — successful outcomes
- `showWarning(message)` — non-blocking warnings
- `showInfo(message)` — neutral information
- `showLoading(message)` — long-running actions
- `showPromise(promise, { loading, success, error })` — lifecycle toasts

## Icon consistency

Keep icon sizing and choice inside the helpers so screens stay visually consistent.

## Example (after helpers exist)

```tsx
import { showError, showSuccess } from '@/app/utils/toast-helpers';

try {
  await saveSomething();
  showSuccess('Saved successfully');
} catch {
  showError('Failed to save');
}
```
